trying to decide if hysterectomy is right for me i am having the second d c done since march in a few days to help with heavy bleeding my gyn says that if this don't help i may have to consider a hysterectomy i am with children and know we don't want anymore my mom and both grandmothers and a few aunts have all had hysterectomies i have tried birth control but still have severe cramps and heavy bleeding i just want to know about any expieriences other women have had the info on the net is so overwhelming it's a very hard decision to make if you have to have the hyst then do it an old saying my grandma told me was take the nursery leave the playpen i had to have one at due to medical problems i only had one son i wanted a daughter but as fate had it if i had tried waited to have a daughter i would not been alive right now the surgery itself was not bad painful for a couple days no lifting no driving weak a few days had to stay off work weeks even though i felt fine emotionally i did fine alot of people told me i would fell less of a women well i felt the same really i felt better i was more open sex was great it didn't affect my drive at all if you go into it with the attitude that it isn't going to change you as a person you will do fine also one note i did keep my ovaries the doctor said this does make a difference as i will go thru menopause normal like everyone else i would highly reccommend keeping them or at least one of them if possible for the hormones Endometriosis Hysterectomy Menstrual cycle Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Prostate cancer Miscarriage Childbirth Breastfeeding Urinary incontinence Androgen insensitivity syndrome Transsexuality Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Stomach cancer Endometrial cancer Sex reassignment surgery female-to-male Intersex surgery Knots Landing Social rule Homosexuality and transgender The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Days of our Lives History of intersex surgery Gynaecology Ovarian cancer Menopause EastEnders Oral contrace